### Assign user1 to HR role at Acme Corp
POST http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user1",
  "companyId": "acme",
  "role": "HR"
}

### Assign user1 to ECONOMY role at Globex
POST http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user1",
  "companyId": "globex",
  "role": "ECONOMY"
}

### Assign user2 to ADMIN role at Acme (inherits HR and ECONOMY)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user2",
  "companyId": "acme",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

### Check if user1 has HR role at Acme (should be true)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check?userId=user1&companyId=acme&role=HR

### Check if user1 has HR role at Globex (should be false)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check?userId=user1&companyId=globex&role=HR

### Check if user2 (admin at Acme) has HR role at Acme (should be true via inheritance)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check?userId=user2&companyId=acme&role=HR

### Check if user2 (admin at Acme) has ECONOMY role at Acme (should be true via inheritance)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check?userId=user2&companyId=acme&role=ECONOMY

### Get all roles for user1 (HR at Acme, ECONOMY at Globex)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/user/user1

### Get all roles for user2 (ADMIN, HR, ECONOMY at Acme)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/user/user2

### Remove specific role (HR) from user1 at Acme
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/user/user1/company/acme/role/HR

### Remove all roles from user1 at Globex
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/user/user1/company/globex

### Remove all roles from user1 (all companies)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/user/user1

### ---- TASK-BASED PERMISSION CHECKS ----

### Check if user1 can list employees (HR task - should be true if user1 has HR role)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user1&companyId=acme&task=LIST_EMPLOYEES

### Check if user1 can view employee (HR task)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user1&companyId=acme&task=VIEW_EMPLOYEE

### Check if user1 can edit employee (HR task)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user1&companyId=acme&task=EDIT_EMPLOYEE

### Check if user1 can read reports (Economy task - should be false if user1 only has HR role)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user1&companyId=acme&task=READ_REPORTS

### Check if user1 can create report (Economy task)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user1&companyId=acme&task=CREATE_REPORT

### Check if user2 (admin) can list employees (should be true via admin inheritance)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user2&companyId=acme&task=LIST_EMPLOYEES

### Check if user2 (admin) can read reports (should be true via admin inheritance)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/permissions/check-task?userId=user2&companyId=acme&task=READ_REPORTS
